<L>__{exterior dauntless stern morning}
<A>__{sailors make their way down a rope ladder, crowd onto the jolly mon. will pushes hard against the windlass, to no avail ... the anchor is too heavy for one man. jack notices.}
<C>__{jack}
<D>__{a little help?}
<A>__{gillette shrugs, gestures to murtogg and mullroy. the three men throw their weight into the windlass, and it turns. jack's pistol is on them the whole time.}
<C>__{murtogg}
<D>__{i can't believe he's doing this.}
<A>__{the windless turns, bringing mullroy into view.}
<C>__{mullroy}
<D>__{you didn't believe he was telling the truth, either.}
<A>__{the windless turns some more, and there's gillette.}
<C>__{gillette}
<P>__{(over his shoulder, to will)}
<D>__{do you have any idea, boy, what you're doing?}
<A>__{another quarter turn }
<C>__{will}
<D>__{no.}
